==English==
===Etymology===
Via French ''[[amender]]'', "to amend", from Latin ''[[emendare]]'', from ''[[ex-]]'', "out of", + ''[[mendum]]'', "fault". Confer aphetic "[[mend]]".
=== Verb ===
'''to amend''' (amends, amended, amending) (''transitive'' or ''intransitive'')
# To make or become [[better]]; to [[improve]]
# To make a [[formal]] [[alteration]] in [[legislation]] by [[adding]], [[deleting]], or [[rephrasing]]
====Synonyms====
